{% block content %}
	<div class="card">
		<h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

		<section class="faq-section">
			<h3>What is Grocery Guru?</h3>
			<p>Grocery Guru is a simple grocery list manager that helps you keep track of items you need to buy.</p>
		</section>

		<section class="faq-section">
			<h3>How do I add items to my list?</h3>
			<p>Click "Add items" in the navbar or from the home page, then enter the item name, quantity, and list name. Your items will be saved to your account.</p>
		</section>

		<section class="faq-section">
			<h3>Can I have multiple shopping lists?</h3>
			<p>Yes! When adding an item, you can specify the list name (e.g., "Weekly groceries", "Party supplies"). Each list keeps its items organized.</p>
		</section>

		<section class="faq-section">
			<h3>How do I switch between light and dark mode?</h3>
			<p>Click the theme toggle in the header. The moon icon appears in light mode (click to switch to dark), and the sun icon appears in dark mode (click to switch to light). Your preference is saved automatically.</p>
		</section>

		<section class="faq-section">
			<h3>Is my data secure?</h3>
			<p>We take your privacy seriously. Your grocery lists are stored securely and associated only with your account.</p>
		</section>
	</div>
{% endblock %}
